  "title": "Promoter 6-15th Feb ($13/hr)",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a friendly and responsible <strong>Food Promoter</strong> to work in a supermarket setting, promoting and selling seafood products such as <strong>Hokkaido</strong> <strong>scallops and crab sticks for hotpot</strong>. The promoter will be required to prepare samples by steaming products using an induction cooker, engage customers, and drive sales.</p><h2>Key Responsibilities</h2><ul><li><p>Promote and sell seafood products (scallops, crab sticks, etc.) to customers</p></li><li><p>Steam food items using an induction cooker according to provided guidelines</p></li><li><p>Offer product samples and explain product features, cooking methods, and promotions</p></li><li><p>Maintain cleanliness and hygiene of the workstation at all times</p></li><li><p>Ensure food safety standards are followed during preparation and handling</p></li><li><p>Monitor stock levels and inform supervisor when replenishment is needed</p></li><li><p>Provide friendly customer service and answer basic customer enquiries<br /></p></li></ul><h2>Requirements</h2><ul><li><p>Comfortable handling and preparing food (seafood)</p></li><li><p>Able to operate an induction cooker (training provided)</p></li><li><p>Good communication skills; able to approach and interact with customer</p></li><li><p>Prior experience as a food promoter or in retail is an advantage (but not mandatory)</p></li><li><p>Food Hygiene Certificate preferred (or willing to obtain)<br /></p><p>Interested candidates please forward resume in MS Word to royhuang@recruitexpress.com.sg</p><p></p><p>Roy Huang Peijie</p><p>CEI No: R1104471</p><p>EA License No. 99C4599</p><p>RCB No. 199601303W</p><p></p><p></p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.<br /></p></li></ul>",
